{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This session is on natural wonders,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and the bigger conference is on the pursuit of happiness."},{"time":5000,"text":"I want to try to combine them all,"},{"time":6000,"text":"because to me, healing is really the ultimate natural wonder."},{"time":9000,"text":"Your body has a remarkable capacity to begin healing itself,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and much more quickly than people had once realized,"},{"time":16000,"text":"if you simply stop doing what’s causing the problem."},{"time":19000,"text":"And so, really, so much of what we do in medicine and life in general"},{"time":23000,"text":"is focused on mopping up the floor without also turning off the faucet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"I love doing this work, because it really gives many people"},{"time":31000,"text":"new hope and new choices that they didn’t have before,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and it allows us to talk about things that -- not just diet,"},{"time":38000,"text":"but that happiness is not --"},{"time":40000,"text":"we're talking about the pursuit of happiness,"},{"time":42000,"text":"but when you really look at all the spiritual traditions,"},{"time":44000,"text":"what Aldous Huxley called the \"perennial wisdom,\""},{"time":47000,"text":"when you get past the named and forms and rituals that really divide people,"},{"time":51000,"text":"it’s really about -- our nature is to be happy;"},{"time":53000,"text":"our nature is to be peaceful, our nature is to be healthy."},{"time":56000,"text":"And so it’s not something -- happiness is not something you get,"},{"time":59000,"text":"health is generally not something that you get."},{"time":61000,"text":"But rather all of these different practices --"},{"time":64000,"text":"you know, the ancient swamis and rabbis and priests and monks and nuns"},{"time":67000,"text":"didn’t develop these techniques to just manage stress"},{"time":70000,"text":"or lower your blood pressure, unclog your arteries,"},{"time":72000,"text":"even though it can do all those things."},{"time":74000,"text":"They’re powerful tools for transformation,"},{"time":76000,"text":"for quieting down our mind and bodies"},{"time":79000,"text":"to allow us to experience what it feels like to be happy,"},{"time":82000,"text":"to be peaceful, to be joyful"},{"time":84000,"text":"and to realize that it’s not something that you pursue and get,"},{"time":87000,"text":"but rather it’s something that you have already until you disturb it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"I studied yoga for many years with a teacher named Swami Satchidananda"},{"time":95000,"text":"and people would say, \"What are you, a Hindu?\" He’d say, \"No, I’m an undo.\""},{"time":98000,"text":"And it’s really about identifying what’s causing us"},{"time":101000,"text":"to disturb our innate health and happiness,"},{"time":104000,"text":"and then to allow that natural healing to occur."},{"time":107000,"text":"To me, that’s the real natural wonder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"So, within that larger context,"},{"time":111000,"text":"we can talk about diet, stress management --"},{"time":114000,"text":"which are really these spiritual practices --"},{"time":116000,"text":"moderate exercise, smoking cessation, support groups and community --"},{"time":120000,"text":"which I’ll talk more about -- and some vitamins and supplements."},{"time":122000,"text":"And it’s not a diet."},{"time":124000,"text":"You know, when most people think about the diet I recommend,"},{"time":126000,"text":"they think it’s a really strict diet."},{"time":128000,"text":"For reversing disease, that’s what it takes,"},{"time":130000,"text":"but if you’re just trying to be healthy, you have a spectrum of choices."},{"time":132000,"text":"And to the degree that you can move in a healthy direction,"},{"time":135000,"text":"you’re going to live longer, you’re going to feel better,"},{"time":137000,"text":"you’re going to lose weight, and so on."},{"time":139000,"text":"And in our studies, what we’ve been able to do"},{"time":141000,"text":"is to use very expensive, high-tech, state-of-the-art measures"},{"time":144000,"text":"to prove how powerful these very simple and low-tech and low-cost --"},{"time":148000,"text":"and in many ways, ancient -- interventions, can be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"We first began by looking at heart disease,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and when I began doing this work 26 or 27 years ago,"},{"time":156000,"text":"it was thought that once you have heart disease it can only get worse."},{"time":160000,"text":"And what we found was that, instead of getting worse and worse,"},{"time":162000,"text":"in many cases it could get better and better,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and much more quickly than people had once realized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"This is a representative patient who at the time was 73 --"},{"time":170000,"text":"totally needed to have a bypass, decided to do this instead."},{"time":173000,"text":"We used quantitative arteriography, showing the narrowing."},{"time":176000,"text":"This is one of the arteries that feed the heart, one of the main arteries,"},{"time":179000,"text":"and you can see the narrowing here."},{"time":181000,"text":"A year later, it’s not as clogged; normally, it goes the other direction."},{"time":184000,"text":"These minor changes in blockages"},{"time":186000,"text":"caused a 300 percent improvement in blood flow,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and using cardiac positron emission tomography, or \"PET,\" scans,"},{"time":192000,"text":"blue and black is no blood flow, orange and white is maximal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"Huge differences can occur without drugs, without surgery."},{"time":199000,"text":"Clinically, he literally couldn’t walk across the street without getting severe chest pain;"},{"time":203000,"text":"within a month, like most people, was pain-free, and within a year,"},{"time":206000,"text":"climbing more than 100 floors a day on a Stairmaster."},{"time":208000,"text":"This is not unusual, and it’s part of what enables people"},{"time":211000,"text":"to maintain these kinds of changes,"},{"time":213000,"text":"because it makes such a big difference in their quality of life."},{"time":215000,"text":"Overall, if you looked at all the arteries in all the patients,"},{"time":218000,"text":"they got worse and worse, from one year to five years, in the comparison group."},{"time":221000,"text":"This is the natural history of heart disease,"},{"time":223000,"text":"but it’s really not natural because we found it could get better and better,"},{"time":227000,"text":"and much more quickly than people had once thought."},{"time":229000,"text":"We also found that the more people change, the better they got."},{"time":232000,"text":"It wasn’t a function of how old or how sick they were --"},{"time":235000,"text":"it was mainly how much they changed,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and the oldest patients improved as much as the young ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"I got this as a Christmas card a few years ago"},{"time":241000,"text":"from two of the patients in one of our programs."},{"time":243000,"text":"The younger brother is 86, the older one’s 95;"},{"time":246000,"text":"they wanted to show me how much more flexible they were."},{"time":248000,"text":"And the following year they sent me this one, which I thought was kind of funny."},{"time":250000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":252000,"text":"You just never know."},{"time":254000,"text":"And what we found was that 99 percent of the patients"},{"time":256000,"text":"start to reverse the progression of their heart disease."},{"time":259000,"text":"Now I thought, you know, if we just did good science,"},{"time":261000,"text":"that would change medical practice. But, that was a little naive."},{"time":263000,"text":"It’s important, but not enough."},{"time":265000,"text":"Because we doctors do what we get paid to do,"},{"time":267000,"text":"and we get trained to do what we get paid to do,"},{"time":269000,"text":"so if we change insurance, then we change medical practice and medical education."},{"time":273000,"text":"Insurance will cover the bypass, it’ll cover the angioplasty;"},{"time":275000,"text":"it won’t, until recently, cover diet and lifestyle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"So, we began through our nonprofit institute's"},{"time":280000,"text":"training hospitals around the country,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and we found that most people could avoid surgery,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and not only was it medically effective, it was also cost effective."},{"time":287000,"text":"And the insurance companies found"},{"time":289000,"text":"that they began to save almost 30,000 dollars per patient,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and Medicare is now in the middle of doing a demonstration project"},{"time":295000,"text":"where they’re paying for 1,800 people to go through the program"},{"time":297000,"text":"on the sites that we train."},{"time":299000,"text":"The fortuneteller says, \"I give smokers a discount"},{"time":301000,"text":"because there’s not as much to tell.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":304000,"text":"I like this slide, because it’s a chance to talk about"},{"time":308000,"text":"what really motivates people to change, and what doesn’t."},{"time":310000,"text":"And what doesn’t work is fear of dying,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and that’s what’s normally used."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Everybody who smokes knows it’s not good for you,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and still 30 percent of Americans smoke --"},{"time":318000,"text":"80 percent in some parts of the world. Why do people do it?"},{"time":321000,"text":"Well, because it helps them get through the day."},{"time":323000,"text":"And I’ll talk more about this, but the real epidemic"},{"time":326000,"text":"isn’t just heart disease or obesity or smoking -- it’s loneliness and depression."},{"time":329000,"text":"As one woman said, \"I’ve got 20 friends in this package of cigarettes,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and they’re always there for me and nobody else is."},{"time":335000,"text":"You’re going to take away my 20 friends? What are you going to give me?\""},{"time":337000,"text":"Or they eat when they get depressed,"},{"time":339000,"text":"or they use alcohol to numb the pain,"},{"time":341000,"text":"or they work too hard, or watch too much TV."},{"time":343000,"text":"There are lots of ways we have of avoiding and numbing and bypassing pain,"},{"time":347000,"text":"but the point of all of this is to deal with the cause of the problem."},{"time":350000,"text":"And the pain is not the problem: it’s the symptom."},{"time":352000,"text":"And telling people they’re going to die is too scary to think about,"},{"time":356000,"text":"or, they’re going to get emphysema or heart attack is too scary,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and so they don’t want to think about it, so they don’t."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361000,"text":"The most effective anti-smoking ad was this one."},{"time":363000,"text":"You’ll notice the limp cigarette hanging out of his mouth,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and \"impotence\" -- the headline is, \"Impotent\" -- it’s not emphysema."},{"time":369000,"text":"What was the biggest selling drug of all time"},{"time":371000,"text":"when it was introduced a few years ago?"},{"time":373000,"text":"Viagra, right? Why? Because a lot of guys need it."},{"time":376000,"text":"It’s not like you say, \"Hey Joe, I’m having erectile dysfunction, how about you?\""},{"time":379000,"text":"And yet, look at the number of prescriptions that are being sold."},{"time":382000,"text":"It’s not so much psychological, it’s vascular,"},{"time":385000,"text":"and nicotine makes your arteries constrict."},{"time":387000,"text":"So does cocaine, so does a high fat diet, so does emotional stress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So the very behaviors that we think of as being so sexy in our culture"},{"time":395000,"text":"are the very ones that leave so many people feeling tired,"},{"time":397000,"text":"lethargic, depressed and impotent, and that’s not much fun."},{"time":400000,"text":"But when you change those behaviors, your brain gets more blood,"},{"time":402000,"text":"you think more clearly, you have more energy,"},{"time":404000,"text":"your heart gets more blood in ways I’ve shown you."},{"time":406000,"text":"Your sexual function improves."},{"time":408000,"text":"And these things occur within hours. This is a study: a high fat meal,"},{"time":412000,"text":"and within one or two hours blood-flow is measurably less --"},{"time":414000,"text":"and you’ve all experienced this at Thanksgiving."},{"time":416000,"text":"When you eat a big fatty meal, how do you feel?"},{"time":418000,"text":"You feel kind of sleepy afterwards."},{"time":420000,"text":"On a low-fat meal, the blood flow doesn’t go down -- it even goes up."},{"time":423000,"text":"Many of you have kids, and you know that’s a big change in your lifestyle,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and so people are not afraid to make big changes in lifestyle if they’re worth it."},{"time":431000,"text":"And the paradox is that when you make big changes, you get big benefits,"},{"time":434000,"text":"and you feel so much better so quickly."},{"time":437000,"text":"For many people, those are choices worth making --"},{"time":439000,"text":"not to live longer, but to live better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442000,"text":"I want to talk a little bit about the obesity epidemic,"},{"time":444000,"text":"because it really is a problem."},{"time":446000,"text":"Two-thirds of adults are overweight or obese,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and diabetes in kids and 30-year-olds"},{"time":451000,"text":"has increased 70 percent in the last 10 years. It’s no joke: it’s real."},{"time":455000,"text":"And just to show you this, this is from the CDC."},{"time":458000,"text":"These are not election returns; these are the percentage of people who are overweight."},{"time":461000,"text":"And if you see from '85 to '86 to '87, '88, '89, '90, '91 --"},{"time":468000,"text":"you get a new category, 15 to 20 percent; '92, '93, '94, '95, '96, '97 --"},{"time":475000,"text":"you get a new category; '98, '99, 2000, and 2001."},{"time":480000,"text":"Mississippi, more than 25 percent of people are overweight."},{"time":484000,"text":"Why is this? Well, this is one way to lose weight that works very well ..."},{"time":487000,"text":"but it doesn’t last, which is the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491000,"text":"Now, there’s no mystery in how you lose weight;"},{"time":493000,"text":"you either burn more calories by exercise or you eat fewer calories."},{"time":497000,"text":"Now, one way to eat fewer calories is to eat less food,"},{"time":500000,"text":"which is why you can lose weight on any diet if you eat less food,"},{"time":502000,"text":"or if you restrict entire categories of foods."},{"time":504000,"text":"But the problem is, you get hungry, so it’s hard to keep it off."},{"time":508000,"text":"The other way is to change the type of food."},{"time":510000,"text":"And fat has nine calories per gram,"},{"time":512000,"text":"whereas protein and carbs only have four."},{"time":514000,"text":"So, when you eat less fat, you eat fewer calories without having to eat less food."},{"time":518000,"text":"So you can eat the same amount of food, but you’ll be getting fewer calories"},{"time":521000,"text":"because the food is less dense in calories."},{"time":523000,"text":"And it’s the volume of food that affects satiety, rather than the type of food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527000,"text":"You know, I don’t like talking about the Atkins diet, but I get asked about it every day,"},{"time":529000,"text":"and so I just thought I’d spend a few minutes on that."},{"time":531000,"text":"The myth that you hear about is,"},{"time":533000,"text":"Americans have been told to eat less fat,"},{"time":535000,"text":"the percent of calories from fat is down,"},{"time":537000,"text":"Americans are fatter than ever, therefore fat doesn’t make you fat."},{"time":540000,"text":"It’s a half-truth. Actually, Americans are eating more fat than ever,"},{"time":544000,"text":"and even more carbs. And so the percentage is lower,"},{"time":546000,"text":"the actual amount is higher, and so the goal is to reduce both."},{"time":549000,"text":"Dr. Atkins and I debated each other many times before he died,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and we agreed that Americans eat too many simple carbs,"},{"time":555000,"text":"the \"bad carbs,\" and these are things like --"},{"time":557000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":559000,"text":"-- sugar, white flour, white rice, alcohol. And you get a double whammy:"},{"time":562000,"text":"you get all these calories that don’t fill you up because you’ve removed the fiber,"},{"time":565000,"text":"and they get absorbed quickly so your blood sugar zooms up."},{"time":568000,"text":"Your pancreas makes insulin to bring it back down, which is good."},{"time":571000,"text":"But insulin accelerates the conversion of calories into fat."},{"time":574000,"text":"So, the goal is not to go to pork rinds and bacon and sausages --"},{"time":576000,"text":"these are not health foods --"},{"time":578000,"text":"but to go from \"bad carbs\" to what are called \"good carbs.\""},{"time":580000,"text":"And these are things like whole foods, or unrefined carbs:"},{"time":583000,"text":"fruits, vegetables, whole wheat flour, brown rice, in their natural forms, are rich in fiber."},{"time":588000,"text":"And the fiber fills you up before you get too many calories,"},{"time":591000,"text":"and it slows the absorption so you don’t get that rapid rise in blood sugar."},{"time":595000,"text":"So, and you get all the disease-protective substances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"It’s not just what you exclude from your diet,"},{"time":600000,"text":"but also what you include that’s protective."},{"time":602000,"text":"Just as all carbs are not bad for you, all fats are not bad for you. There are good fats."},{"time":605000,"text":"And these are predominantly what are called the Omega-3 fatty acids."},{"time":608000,"text":"You find these, for example, in fish oil."},{"time":610000,"text":"And the bad fats are things like trans-fatty acids and processed food"},{"time":613000,"text":"and saturated fats, which we find in meat."},{"time":615000,"text":"If you don’t remember anything else from this talk,"},{"time":617000,"text":"three grams a day of fish oil can reduce your risk of a heart attack"},{"time":620000,"text":"and sudden death by 50 to 80 percent."},{"time":622000,"text":"Three grams a day. They come in one-gram capsules;"},{"time":624000,"text":"more than that just gives you extra fat you don’t need."},{"time":626000,"text":"It also helps reduce the risk of the most common cancers"},{"time":629000,"text":"like breast, prostate and colon cancer."},{"time":631000,"text":"Now, the problem with the Atkins diet,"},{"time":633000,"text":"everybody knows people who have lost weight on it,"},{"time":635000,"text":"but you can lose weight on amphetamines, you know, and fen-phen."},{"time":637000,"text":"I mean, there are lots of ways of losing weight that aren’t good for you."},{"time":640000,"text":"You want to lose weight in a way that enhances your health"},{"time":642000,"text":"rather than the one that harms it."},{"time":644000,"text":"And the problem is that it’s based on this half-truth,"},{"time":646000,"text":"which is that Americans eat too many simple carbs,"},{"time":649000,"text":"so if you eat fewer simple carbs you’re going to lose weight."},{"time":651000,"text":"You’ll lose even more weight if you go to whole foods and less fat,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and you’ll enhance your health rather than harming it."},{"time":656000,"text":"He says, \"I’ve got some good news."},{"time":658000,"text":"While your cholesterol level has remained the same,"},{"time":660000,"text":"the research findings have changed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":662000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Now, what happens to your heart when you go on an Atkins diet?"},{"time":666000,"text":"The red is good at the beginning, and a year later --"},{"time":668000,"text":"this is from a study done in a peer-reviewed journal called Angiology --"},{"time":672000,"text":"there’s more red after a year on a diet like I would recommend,"},{"time":675000,"text":"there’s less red, less blood flow after a year on an Atkins-type diet."},{"time":678000,"text":"So, yes, you can lose weight, but your heart isn’t happy."},{"time":682000,"text":"Now, one of the studies funded by the Atkins Center"},{"time":684000,"text":"found that 70 percent of the people were constipated, 65 percent had bad breath,"},{"time":688000,"text":"54 percent had headaches – this is not a healthy way to eat."},{"time":692000,"text":"And so, you might start to lose weight and start to attract people towards you,"},{"time":695000,"text":"but when they get too close it’s going to be a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":699000,"text":"And more seriously, there are case reports now of 16-year-old girls"},{"time":702000,"text":"who died after a few weeks on the Atkins diet --"},{"time":704000,"text":"of bone disease, kidney disease, and so on."},{"time":706000,"text":"And that’s how your body excretes waste, is through your breath,"},{"time":708000,"text":"your bowels and your perspiration."},{"time":710000,"text":"So when you go on these kinds of diet, they begin to smell bad."},{"time":713000,"text":"So, an optimal diet is low in fat, low in the bad carbs,"},{"time":717000,"text":"high in the good carbs and enough of the good fats."},{"time":719000,"text":"And then, again, it’s a spectrum:"},{"time":721000,"text":"when you move in this direction, you’re going to lose weight,"},{"time":723000,"text":"you’re going to feel better and you’re going to gain health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"Now, there are ecological reasons for eating lower on the food chain too,"},{"time":729000,"text":"whether it’s the deforestation of the Amazon, or making more protein available,"},{"time":733000,"text":"to the four billion people who live on a dollar a day --"},{"time":736000,"text":"not to mention whatever ethical concerns people have."},{"time":738000,"text":"So, there are lots of reasons for eating this way that go beyond just your health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":742000,"text":"Now, we’re about to publish the first study"},{"time":744000,"text":"looking at the effects of this program on prostate cancer,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and, in collaboration with Sloane-Kettering and with UCSF."},{"time":751000,"text":"We took 90 men who had biopsy-proven prostate cancer"},{"time":755000,"text":"and who had elected, for reasons unrelated to the study, not to have surgery."},{"time":758000,"text":"We could randomly divide them into two groups,"},{"time":760000,"text":"and then we could have one group"},{"time":762000,"text":"that is a non-intervention control group to compare to,"},{"time":764000,"text":"which we can’t do with, say, breast cancer, because everyone gets treated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"What we found was that, after a year,"},{"time":769000,"text":"none of the experimental group patients"},{"time":771000,"text":"who made these lifestyle changes needed treatment,"},{"time":773000,"text":"whereas six of the control-group patients needed surgery or radiation."},{"time":776000,"text":"When we looked at their PSA levels -- which is a marker for prostate cancer --"},{"time":780000,"text":"they got worse in the control group,"},{"time":782000,"text":"but they actually got better in the experimental group,"},{"time":784000,"text":"and these differences were highly significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":786000,"text":"And then I wondered: was there any relationship"},{"time":788000,"text":"between how much people changed their diet and lifestyle --"},{"time":790000,"text":"whichever group they were in -- and the changes in PSA?"},{"time":792000,"text":"And sure enough, we found a dose-response relationship,"},{"time":795000,"text":"just like we found in the arterial blockages in our cardiac studies."},{"time":798000,"text":"And in order for the PSA to go down, they had to make pretty big changes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801000,"text":"I then wondered, well, maybe they’re just changing their PSA,"},{"time":804000,"text":"but it’s not really affecting the tumor growth."},{"time":806000,"text":"So we took some of their blood serum and sent it down to UCLA;"},{"time":809000,"text":"they added it to a standard line of prostate tumor cells growing in tissue culture,"},{"time":813000,"text":"and it inhibited the growth seven times more"},{"time":815000,"text":"in the experimental group than in the control group -- 70 versus 9 percent."},{"time":820000,"text":"And finally, I said, I wonder if there’s any relationship between"},{"time":822000,"text":"how much people change and how it inhibited their tumor growth,"},{"time":825000,"text":"whichever group they happened to be in."},{"time":826000,"text":"And this really got me excited because again,"},{"time":828000,"text":"we found the same pattern: the more people change,"},{"time":831000,"text":"the more it affected the growth of their tumors."},{"time":834000,"text":"And finally, we did MRI and MR spectroscopy scans on some of these patients,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and the tumor activity is shown in red in this patient,"},{"time":839000,"text":"and you can see clearly it’s better a year later, along with the PSA going down."},{"time":843000,"text":"So, if it’s true for prostate cancer, it’ll almost certainly be true for breast cancer as well."},{"time":847000,"text":"And whether or not you have conventional treatment,"},{"time":849000,"text":"in addition, if you make these changes, it may help reduce the risk of recurrence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"The last thing I want to talk about, apropos of the issue of the pursuit of happiness,"},{"time":857000,"text":"is that study after study have shown"},{"time":859000,"text":"that people who are lonely and depressed --"},{"time":861000,"text":"and depression is the other real epidemic in our culture --"},{"time":864000,"text":"are many times more likely to get sick and die prematurely,"},{"time":867000,"text":"in part because, as we talked about, they’re more likely to smoke"},{"time":870000,"text":"and overeat and drink too much and work too hard and so on."},{"time":873000,"text":"But also, through mechanisms that we don’t fully understand,"},{"time":876000,"text":"people who are lonely and depressed are many times --"},{"time":878000,"text":"three to five to ten times, in some studies --"},{"time":880000,"text":"more likely to get sick and die prematurely."},{"time":882000,"text":"And depression is treatable. We need to do something about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":885000,"text":"Now, on the other hand, anything that promotes intimacy is healing."},{"time":888000,"text":"It can be sexual intimacy –"},{"time":890000,"text":"I happen to think that healing energy and erotic energy"},{"time":892000,"text":"are just different forms of the same thing."},{"time":894000,"text":"Friendship, altruism, compassion, service – all the perennial truths that we talked about"},{"time":899000,"text":"that are part of all religion and all cultures --"},{"time":901000,"text":"once you stop trying to see the differences,"},{"time":904000,"text":"these are the things in our own self-interest,"},{"time":906000,"text":"because they free us from our suffering and from disease."},{"time":910000,"text":"And it’s in a sense the most selfish thing that we can do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914000,"text":"Just take a look at one study. This was done by David Spiegel at Stanford."},{"time":917000,"text":"He took women with metastatic breast cancer,"},{"time":919000,"text":"randomly divided them into two groups."},{"time":921000,"text":"One group of people just met for an hour-and-a-half once a week in a support group."},{"time":924000,"text":"It was a nurturing, loving environment,"},{"time":926000,"text":"where they were encouraged to let down their emotional defenses"},{"time":928000,"text":"and talk about how awful it is to have breast cancer"},{"time":930000,"text":"with people who understood, because they were going through it too."},{"time":932000,"text":"They just met once a week for a year."},{"time":934000,"text":"Five years later, those women lived twice as long, and you can see that the people --"},{"time":938000,"text":"and that was the only difference between the groups."},{"time":940000,"text":"It was a randomized control study published in The Lancet."},{"time":942000,"text":"Other studies have shown this as well."},{"time":945000,"text":"So, these simple things that create intimacy are really healing,"},{"time":947000,"text":"and even the word healing, it comes from the root \"to make whole.\""},{"time":950000,"text":"The word yoga comes from the Sanskrit,"},{"time":952000,"text":"meaning \"union, to yoke, to bring together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"And the last slide I want to show you is from -- I was -- again,"},{"time":958000,"text":"this swami that I studied with for so many years, and I"},{"time":960000,"text":"did a combined oncology and cardiology Grand Rounds"},{"time":963000,"text":"at the University of Virginia medical school a couple of years ago."},{"time":965000,"text":"And at the end of it, somebody said,"},{"time":967000,"text":"\"Hey, Swami, what’s the difference between wellness and illness?\""},{"time":971000,"text":"And so he went up on the board and he wrote the word \"illness,\""},{"time":973000,"text":"and circled the first letter, and then wrote the word \"wellness,\""},{"time":976000,"text":"and circled the first two letters ..."},{"time":978000,"text":"To me, it’s just shorthand for what we’re talking about:"},{"time":980000,"text":"that anything that creates a sense of connection"},{"time":982000,"text":"and community and love is really healing."},{"time":985000,"text":"And then we can enjoy our lives more fully without getting sick in the process."},{"time":990000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}